# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Root .gitignore
#
# Per-package node_modules, dist, etc. are handled by per-package .gitignores
# under backend/, frontend/, cli/, agents/mapper/. This file handles the
# repo-wide generated artifacts under agents/ that aren't checked in.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
.vscode/
.idea/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# agents/graphify/ — generated outputs
#
# Tracked under agents/graphify/:
#   *.py, *.sh, README.md, .gitignore               (tooling)
#   <package>-module-level/MODULE_RELATIONSHIPS.md  (text Mermaid for diff/PR)
#   <package>-module-level/MODULE_RELATIONSHIPS_features-only.md
#
# Everything else is regenerated from agents/codebase-map/*.json by:
#   agents/graphify/map-module.sh
#   agents/graphify/build-mermaid.py
#   agents/graphify/build-neighborhoods.py
#   agents/graphify/build-explorer.py
#   agents/graphify/build-module-level.py
#   agents/graphify/build-unified.py
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Ignore every subdirectory under agents/graphify/ by default.
agents/graphify/*/

# Then re-include the per-package "*-module-level" directories so the
# MODULE_RELATIONSHIPS*.md files inside them can be tracked.
!agents/graphify/*-module-level/

# Within those re-included dirs, ignore the generated HTML and the
# graphify-out/ subdir.
agents/graphify/*-module-level/*.html
agents/graphify/*-module-level/graphify-out/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# agents/codebase-map/ — mapper JSON sidecars are regenerable, large,
# not human-diffable. The .md files there are LLM-enriched narratives
# and worth committing.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
agents/codebase-map/*.json
